For the past few years, the writer Gu Xiang has lived in a village near the mouth of the Yangtze River, and even the outbreak has not forced her to leave. In rural areas, unlike cities, there is no need to worry about segregation. Every household grows its own fresh vegetables. For the elderly left behind in the countryside, the outbreak does not seem to have aroused their guard, they are more concerned about the survey team left around the village hole.

It's nice to feel small

By Gu Xiang

On February 9th, our village was sealed up, too, with a pass to get out. Villages and communities are not the same, no walls, no doors, is a roadside pile of small houses, here a pile, there a cluster, is a village, a village of different brigade. So they closed off a road at the entrance to the village. The small bridge on the southwest side, the bridge on the northwest side, and the path through the woods leading to the bridge on the north side were all blocked off. Together with another brigade from the same village, every path was closed off, they are serious about sealing, not just in the village for show.

The same is true in other villages nearby. For example, there is a village, in our village to more like a city on the road, the road through the village, the village closed, people can not go through the village. The courier could no longer navigate his way out of the impassable. On the morning of my first day in Fengcun, when I didn't know the village had been sealed off, I ordered a delivery from Carrefour. On my mobile phone, I saw little brother leaving, and I went out to wait for him. On the way, I saw him double back on the way, thought "what's the matter" , went to the village only to find a road closure, thought of the trouble he encountered, suddenly felt sorry for him, I said I was not in a hurry, return goods can also, see you want what I can. As it turned out, he set off again, circling the map, and finally brought it to me, still very pleasant and cheerful, not at all angry at having sent such a troublesome order. After that, I stopped ordering takeout and takeout, because they might not all know the way around here, and it would be too much trouble to find their own way around. I think it's better if I live alone in the corner village and don't bother them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
What about the rest of the village? Local people are some old people, many do not have mobile phones and computers, but they have a point is very easy, that they have a lot of fresh vegetables, have reservations. Once again, I felt: it's so good to have land. Tolstoj wrote how much land does a man need, and the hero of the story is so greedy that he ends up needing only six feet of land from head to toe, he got a piece of land of his own, "You can farm your own land, Make Hay on your own land, cut down your own trees, and graze your cattle on your own pasture. There was joy in his heart when he went to till the fields or to see the crops and the meadows, where the grass and the flowers in bloom stood out to him. As long as you grow a little something on the balcony, you will understand the mood. If I can grow even a small piece of food, I can have a more stable heart. And the Grapes of Wrath: "even if he doesn't succeed, as long as he has land, he won't feel small. "

But My neighbors will soon have no private land because of the demolition. Before the Spring Festival, the two next to the brigade has been negotiated, was asked to move before the first half of the month. But because of the epidemic, now do not have to move out, can not rent a house, can not move. According to them, they were given a rental allowance of 12 yuan per square meter for the purpose of building a new house in 2022 in an area where the old house had not yet been demolished. Only our village has not officially said when it will be demolished, "because we are 'peasants going to the city' , you are 'demolishing' , not the same, you will probably be better, " said the people of the neighboring brigade to our brigade. My neighbors "Wang Yi don't move, " because demolition is not good, is not the legendary "demolition will get rich, " can not get rich, but also very troublesome, they are 70 or 80 years old, moving would take away their decades old beds, wardrobes, cupboards, dressers, tables, chairs and stools. They wouldn't buy new furniture. It was very old and heavy, with bad hinges, but the wood was probably good. When will be relocated only speculation, some people say that broad beans also can not eat, some people say that corn can eat two crops. Do not know when to move, the land is planted, "no matter when to move, Rice must eat AH, " and not afraid of the white race, the kind can not eat. Now, broad beans have grown up, I think it is possible to eat broad beans.

A little over a year ago, the demolition started to feel a little real. The factories around were all torn down. The night before Christmas Eve, the power was cut off. I went out to see if there was no electricity in my house or in the whole village. I saw the tall steel frames of factories and warehouses stooping high in the air, and finally huddled together, like a giant spider sucked dry and turned into a thin, brittle shell. Then I watched the diggers for many days. The diggers folded and pressed the roofs and walls into a flexible mass. The diggers were followed by egrets. They were afraid of people, but not of the diggers. The buildings to be demolished had long ago been marked with a circle, a "t" or a large dot. I had seen this symbol long ago, but I hadn't noticed it. It was as if the forty thieves had marked the intended door. The walls had been whitewashed only a short time before they were torn down, and the workers had been asked to paint a number of clumsy pictures: Lotus, plum blossom, Kong Rong Rang Pear, and various slogans. Even if tomorrow's the day, today's the day. Even for tomorrow to tear down, today specially decorated, this is also a matter of farmers know. The village garden also installed a new fence, 300 yuan a piece, only by the road outside that piece of installed, there is no. My door was also hung a "most beautiful courtyard" of the small card, I went to the village a look, every family have. Then the factory became a wasteland, quickly covered with weeds, although not very large, still have a little "wilderness" feeling. At that time, the old woman in the village took me to see two new holes in the village. One was on the ridge of the field, covered with a big stone, and the other was on the village side road. She was small and bent down to look under the parked car, when he found it, he said, "here! See? " The hole was about the size of a rice bowl, it was filled in the middle, like a pen cap pressed into a circle on an arm, or a cowpox mark, "yes, that's it, " she said contentedly. This was the proof that someone had come to survey our village.

Before the Spring Festival, the survey team appeared around the village. They dug holes everywhere. In the woods and along the riverbanks, there was an orange-colored machine, like the sci-fi avatars who sense the presence of outsiders. The old woman went to show me the signs on the ground. If they dug a hole in the vegetable field, they would pay the owner 300 yuan, but they did not dig a hole in the vegetable field. On those days, they set up green tents and lived in them on the southeast side of the village. Three large green tents were set up on the southwest side of the village on those days. At night, the light shone through the tents. The fire in the big stove could be seen roaring in the cold wind and was colorless. It was Tofu rice cooked for the whole village by a dragon service, the meal was eaten in another Green Shed, three times in twenty days. Farmers are becoming fewer and fewer, getting old, dying, going to the city, living in buildings, having no land to grow, going to the supermarket to buy vegetables, and those who have their own land and their own land will soon be gone, won't they?

And then, like, everything just stopped. Only the arrival of spring will not be stopped. You can feel spring in the light, the light is so bright, and the Veronica Persica, the grass, the clouds, the water, all new, glowing, soft and tender, nature is older than we are, we are young and old, and life is short.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the village, I said casually to the old woman, some places have killed people's cats. The result unexpectedly is, she immediately interjects: "PRETTY GOOD! " I was really shocked. In her vegetable garden, cats lay in disorder, strolling, some lying at her feet. She did not seem to be a cat-hater at all. She was usually kind and timid, and every day was a beautiful picture to her, however, in my various explanations, she still felt that she supported the cat-killing initiative. Although I had never had any idealized picture of peasant or country life, her answer struck me as so easy and disapproving a brute as an ordinary man. Thinking of Gaz, he wrote of the villagers: "Last night they even went to the church, humble and obedient as a flock of sheep, and today they can tear it down without mercy" (my university) . She wasn't even trying to protect herself, she had no defenses, she didn't wear a mask when she talked to me, she stood very close to me, she wanted to be close to me, I stepped back, she would follow me, I turned half way around, she would take another step, as if she knew me and I was safe standing there. I don't think it's a good time to talk to the neighbors these days, which reduces the chances of seeing her.

Before the village was sealed, I went for a walk. It was deserted. No one was here. Even if there was no epidemic, it was empty. Occasionally saw people, far away, some people wearing masks in the river fishing. The old river is crooked, the new river is straight. I walked up the dirt slope to get around them. The slope was heaped up not long ago by digging a river, and the place where the slope was once a village. The people who had moved from the village came back here to cultivate and cultivate the slope where their village was buried, grow full of vegetables, people are really hard-working, love to grow things in the field. Far up the slope, there were women at work. The woods are full of birds. It's lovely. Think of it as a world without people, and then it's like time is gone. The closer you get to the outer ring, the louder the traffic sounds and the human world is still running on it. One afternoon I was on the Bank of the river when I was attracted by the sound of a bird squawking, like a squawk from a small rubber ball: Poof, poof, poof, poof, poof, poof, poof, poof. Then, on the other side of the road, in another grove, a bird made the same sound, and they answered, and the first bird called, and the second bird called, and I listened for a long time. WHY DO BIRDS SING? Remember "why do the Suans Sing" , also remember Ted Jiang's "great silence" , the last parrot left a human words: "Take Care, I love you

After the roads were closed, I went out for a walk in the afternoon, and the area seemed suddenly very limited. But the next day, I suddenly saw a girl who was still walking along the same road with me, still holding her cell phone watching the walk, but walking outside the fence. She was just out for a walk on her phone, and I don't think she went over the barrier, which means there's an easy way out, and I quickly found the way to the river. I have lived here for many years, and have always been very loitering, and there are still roads I have not yet trod, which I have done in the last few days, before they are all gone. Some roads, which may have been difficult to walk before, have been trodden out these days, and have appeared in a thicket of yellow flowers, in a meadow by a river, or somewhere else. The Woods are so open, you can't surround the field because it's so wild. I tried to get as far as I could without climbing over the fence, only to find that I could go as far as I'd ever gone before, anywhere, and then I'd sneak back in. I went to the last time I saw cattail spray, a wild duck flying away from the water, to the original slope, far away there are still people working. The anglers were still fishing in the forest, one by one, very sparingly, like hermits. Ragweed spiny seeds all over my pant leg. I also saw a flock of small, chestnut-colored, white-bellied birds, like short shuttles, passing through a great mass of dried and prostrate dog-tail grass, pecking at the seeds. I passed by a little, and they flew away without a sound, jump up and down and eat it. It's good to see them. But the beekeeper's cabin in the woods was shut up, and there was no one, no bees, and they did not come, though the rape flowers were already in bloom.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When I got home, I read a book, reread some of Chekhov's novels in the last few days, and read a history of mankind as a time spiraling, as if it were a shell, to see how intelligent and bright people can be, take a look at the vastness of the world, the depth of time, and the people in the book that follows. I think it's good for people to feel small sometimes. People really are small. They shouldn't feel The Hours to feel Not Scared to Die. Stein Baker is not my favorite writer.

In addition to reading, I play a game called "Baba is you, " which is a small but impressive game of pushing boxes. We also have some mysteries in mind that can be solved by playing games. Its world has many rules, and the rules are like poetry: Baba is you, the wall can not move, the stone can be pushed, the Rose is red, love is hot, you are melting, love is winning. I change the rules by pushing words, and sometimes: Baba is me, and the wall is me, and as the wall becomes me, I Florida the wall toward victory. I was touched by that scene.

Not only does the epidemic have a profound impact on our lives today, it will also occupy our memories and change our minds for a long time to come. We need more eyes to continue to observe and document the crises and changes of our time. These are sincere and weighty records, and we will keep them.
